caption.p:
Final structural population pharmacokinetic‐pharmacodynamic model of chloroquine and desethylchloroquine in healthy subjects inoculated with blood‐stage Plasmodium vivax.
Ce, the concentration of the drug in the hypothetical effect compartment;
CLCQ/F, apparent clearance of chloroquine;
CLDCQ/F, apparent clearance of desethylchloroquine; CQ, chloroquine; DCQ, desethylchloroquine;
EC50, the drug concentration producing 50% of the
Emax;
Emax, maximum parasite killing attributable to the drug; FM, fraction of chloroquine metabolized to desethylchloroquine;
Frel, relative bioavailability of first‐order absorption;
Hill, the Hill coefficient;
ka, rate constant of absorption;
ke0 CQ, transfer rate constant from effect compartment of chloroquine;
kgrow, growth rate of P. vivax;
kkill, killing rate of P. vivax by the drug;
Q1CQF, apparent inter‐compartmental clearance between central compartment of chloroquine and peripheral compartment 1 of chloroquine;
Q1DCQF, apparent intercompartmental clearance between central compartment of desethylchloroquine and peripheral compartment one of desethylchloroquine;
Vc CQ/F, apparent volume of distribution for central compartment of chloroquine;
Vc DCQ/F, apparent volume of distribution for central compartment of desethylchloroquine;
Vp1 CQ/F, apparent volume of distribution for peripheral compartment one of chloroquine;
Vp1 DCQ/F, apparent volume of distribution for peripheral compartment one of desethylchloroquine.

fn.p:
AUC0-inf, area under the concentration‐time curve from zero to infinity; CI, confidence interval;
CLCQF, apparent clearance of chloroquine;
CLDCQF, apparent clearance of desethylchloroquine;
Cmax, maximum concentration; CQ, chloroquine; DCQ, desethylchloroquine;
Frel, relative bioavailability of first‐order absorption;
ka, rate constant of absorption;
